# Changelog Guidelines

Follow the [Common Changelog](https://common-changelog.org) style guide when updating `CHANGELOG.md`.

## Format

```markdown
## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD

### Changed

- Description of change ([#123](link)) ([@author](link))

[X.Y.Z]: https://github.com/nmassart/pi-sms/releases/tag/vX.Y.Z
```

## Rules

1. **Date format**: Use ISO 8601 (`YYYY-MM-DD`). Run `date +%Y-%m-%d` to get today's date.
2. **Categories** (in order, only include if applicable):
   - `Changed` - changes in existing functionality
   - `Added` - new features
   - `Removed` - removed features
   - `Fixed` - bug fixes
3. **References**: Link to PR/issue at end of line: `([#123](url))`
4. **Authors**: Credit contributors: `([@name](url))`
5. **Breaking changes**: Prefix with `**Breaking:**` and explain migration
6. **Imperative mood**: Write "Add feature" not "Added feature"
7. **No prefixes**: Don't use `feat:`, `fix:`, etc. - use natural language
8. **Link releases**: Add reference link at bottom for each version

## Example Entry

```markdown
## [0.2.0] - 2026-08-01

### Added

- Support for multiple Trello lists based on sender ([#12](https://github.com/nmassart/pi-sms/pull/12))

### Fixed

- **Breaking:** Rename `poll.interval_seconds` to `poll.interval` ([#10](https://github.com/nmassart/pi-sms/pull/10))

[0.2.0]: https://github.com/nmassart/pi-sms/releases/tag/v0.2.0
```
